solution: ```class Solution {
public:
    int brokenCalc(int startValue, int target) {
        int ops = 0;
        while (target > startValue) {
            if (target % 2 == 1) {
                target += 1;
            } else {
                target /= 2;
            }
            ++ops;
        }
        return ops + (startValue - target);
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log target)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Work backwards from target to startValue. If target is odd, increment; if even, halve. Each halving roughly halves the value, giving logarithmic steps. When target ≤ startValue, only subtractions remain.

